Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.31,0:00:18.34,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}I have a big gun, I took it from my Lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.55,0:00:21.79,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Sick with Justice, I just wanna feel you...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.02,0:00:25.20,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}I'm your angel, only a ring away...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.32,0:00:28.55,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}You make me violate you, no matter who you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.53,0:00:38.67,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}It's all up to you, no one lives forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.87,0:00:42.26,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Been burn in the hell, by all those pigs out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.34,0:00:45.53,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}It's always been hell, from when I was born...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.67,0:00:48.72,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}They make me violate them, no matter who they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.72,0:00:52.26,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fs79}Get down on your knees! Get a good head on your shoulders!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.26,0:00:55.69,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}If it's for your guys, go to the end of the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.69,0:00:59.00,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Do what you think, give it with dedication...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.00,0:01:02.27,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}I'll put out your misery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.36,0:01:05.67,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}You made a mess! For Christ sakes, this rotten world!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.67,0:01:09.10,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Shit out of luck! Go with my vision!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.10,0:01:12.54,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Light up the fire! Right on the power!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.54,0:01:15.90,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Weapon... I have it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.94,0:01:24.48,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Weapon... I have it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.32,0:01:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Are we out of the missiles' range?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.02,0:01:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.42,0:01:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're safe at this distance. Damn them.\NWe'll keep our distance and observe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.58,0:02:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. What the hell are you doing?\NHey, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.29,0:02:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said nothing about detonating it\Nwithout any warning!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.59,0:02:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if we'd flooded the place?\NYour method is too violent!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.53,0:02:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't be screwing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.93,0:02:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more we fuss the less time\Nwe have to do our job.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.03,0:02:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, but you could've said\Nsomething to me ahead of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.47,0:02:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you expect me\Nto talk underwater?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.11,0:02:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could pay closer\Nattention to what I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.87,0:02:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, give me a signal or\Nsomething before...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.74,0:02:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you do anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.28,0:02:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Bones! Bones!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.72,0:02:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well yeah, there're gonna be bones.\NThey're all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.52,0:03:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock, this is a graveyard that people\Nliving on the surface have forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.16,0:03:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's where they reluctantly\Nended their lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.70,0:03:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...when confronted by the Grim Reaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.60,0:03:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No flowers or candles.\NNo one comes and no one remembers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.37,0:03:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A sickening catacomb without any saints.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never liked these kinds of places.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.58,0:03:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It smells like something's rotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.25,0:03:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we stay too long, it'll affect our lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.06,0:03:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Revy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.83,0:03:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you think these guys felt\Nwhile they waited down here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.41,0:03:54.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What went through their minds\Nonce the lights faded...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.28,0:03:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and they struggled to breathe?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.35,0:04:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's too damn gloomy.\NHow do you expect me to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.99,0:04:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dying without air could only\Nfeel like dying without air.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.99,0:04:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How strangers die is just\Nhow strangers die.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.26,0:04:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking about it isn't gonna\Ndo a damned thing, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.93,0:04:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just think of things that won't bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.15,0:04:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this. These guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.86,0:04:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like they had their own\N"Gunfight at the OK Corral" right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.64,0:05:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain! You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.99,0:05:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you shoot the captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.64,0:05:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy, this is probably\Nthe skeleton of the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.94,0:05:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Ahbe guy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.51,0:05:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is his iron cross lying around\Nsomewhere? It'll be worth something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.98,0:05:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.35,0:05:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This guy's uniform is different.\NHe's the SS.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.52,0:05:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the painting?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.72,0:05:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.02,0:05:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's not here it's got to be in a safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.46,0:05:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what made them engage\Nin a gunfight, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.23,0:05:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Panic caused by desperation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.63,0:05:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a laughable theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.74,0:06:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despair is the same as the end of cancer.\NYou've got nothing left to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.51,0:06:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't know the details but this\NGestapo was the one that shot first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.71,0:06:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sailors came in here\Nto avenge their captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.95,0:06:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it ended with the\N"Last Stand at the Alamo".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.15,0:06:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aboard a ship, everyone's\Npractically family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.09,0:06:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They wouldn't have fought amongst\Nthemselves knowing they were gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.56,0:06:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one that would start\Na fight would be the outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.10,0:06:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how it works?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.46,0:06:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.41,0:06:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Rock?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.31,0:06:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the goods?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.54,0:06:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it. It's the same\Nas the image on file.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.01,0:06:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! This is it, Rock! You put it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.42,0:06:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go get the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.39,0:06:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.19,0:06:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what we're after.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.62,0:06:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not kids on an errand, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.23,0:07:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't grab everything that's\Nworth some money, it's a wasted trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.16,0:07:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The captain had an iron cross\Nwith a sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.03,0:07:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a valuable piece with a diamond on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.44,0:07:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little too valuable\Nto leave behind as fish food.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.74,0:07:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.68,0:07:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be back as soon as I've got everything\Nworth taking. Keep those guys company.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.35,0:07:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up. Don't stare.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.76,0:07:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it's the right\Nthing to do either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the distance, Benny-boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.59,0:07:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was 5,200 yards when I last checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.93,0:07:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're well out of range.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.50,0:07:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a dangerous bunch.\NThey're maniacs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.07,0:07:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And seeing that they launched three\Nat once, they're well equipped too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.21,0:07:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're directly above that U-boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.58,0:07:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do a damned thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All soldiers line up in position! Standby\Nfor the Commander's instructions!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.15,0:08:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen! My beloved braves of\Nthe White Aryan Socialist Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.29,0:08:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, at this moment, you will witness...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.16,0:08:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the creation of a new world!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.13,0:08:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In one stroke, we will reclaim\Nthe great order that was lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.40,0:08:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in the great war due to the interference\Nof the Zionists and Communists.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.84,0:08:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True patriots are counting on you,\Ngentlemen on the front lines!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.65,0:08:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an act of courage for\Nstrict order and patriotism!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.42,0:08:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To restore the racial hierarchy\Nto the way it was meant to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.32,0:08:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide Corps, salute!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.83,0:08:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kruppen Feller!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.73,0:08:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the hero chosen\Nto fulfill this objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.00,0:08:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You represent the courage\Nof the Aryan race.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.07,0:08:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There has never... There has never\Nbeen a more glorious moment! I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.34,0:08:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot find words to express\Nthis through my emotion and tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.35,0:09:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm filled with emotion, Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will fulfill this sacred duty\Nat the cost of my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.82,0:09:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commence singing of the anthem!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Raise our flag up high!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.30,0:09:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pave the road ahead of us!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.37,0:09:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We, the strike force...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.51,0:09:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Will firmly march forward!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.51,0:09:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Towards the last battle...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.32,0:09:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.66,0:09:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at this, Dutch.\NThey're holding a concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.10,0:09:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's some distasteful marching song.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.16,0:09:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.60,0:09:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a worthless guy live it up by\Nraising his useless self onto a podium...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.24,0:09:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and you end up with\Na march-loving idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.44,0:10:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a common formula\Nyou'll find anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.38,0:10:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, as a white man?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.85,0:10:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That kinda machismo doesn't\Nagree with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.88,0:10:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I'm Jewish.\N"Fuck the Nazis" was a family creed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.52,0:10:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh right, I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.73,0:10:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, are the beacons on yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.59,0:10:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're both still in the submarine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.46,0:10:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, there's nothing we can\Ndo but pick at each other's politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.67,0:10:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not worried about the job,\Nbut I am worried about the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.54,0:10:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That'll always be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.91,0:10:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we had the time to retrieve it\NI'd take the whole sub back to port.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.61,0:10:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way, I could show those\Nparading idiots...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.62,0:10:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...on that piece of crap ship\Nwhat their Fuhrer went through.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.86,0:10:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.66,0:10:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this isn't good.\NThose guys are up to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.27,0:10:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're lowering a pod.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.53,0:11:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate they're gonna face\Neach other in the submarine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.77,0:11:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do, Dutch?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.27,0:11:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing we can do.\NThey still have TOWs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.48,0:11:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It bugs me to say so, but we'll wait for\Nour chance like a snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.65,0:11:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want, you can pray while you shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.92,0:11:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's about all we can do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.50,0:11:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Phew. Big catch, big catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.60,0:11:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found everything from the iron crosses\Nto stuff maniacs will drool over...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.47,0:11:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a treasure mountain worthy\Nof a grave robber's dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.01,0:11:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.15,0:12:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking a lot and...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.98,0:12:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's leave that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.09,0:12:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.66,0:12:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Thou shalt not steal"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.66,0:12:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you become a priest?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.23,0:12:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not my point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.33,0:12:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those medals are proof of what\Nthese people did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.70,0:12:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have the right to strip\Nthem of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.57,0:12:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If anyone has the right to those medals...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.54,0:12:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it's these people. Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.68,0:12:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was right next to his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.45,0:12:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The captain had this on him\Nright until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.49,0:12:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The captain left his family to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.49,0:12:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To us the medals are nothing\Nbut antiques.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.00,0:12:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But to the people who were left behind\Nthey're priceless memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.21,0:13:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.31,0:13:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Given this location and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.85,0:13:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a story that's\Nperfect for this atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.56,0:13:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you a little secret, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.83,0:13:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.80,0:13:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This, and this. What would\Nyou call these?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.04,0:13:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A medal and a human skull.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.48,0:13:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.61,0:13:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.51,0:13:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you strip away their meanings,\Nthat's all they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.38,0:13:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just the word "things".
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.49,0:13:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you were to once again\Ngive these things meaning...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.52,0:13:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...their value wouldn't be determined\Nby some rosy, so-called memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.96,0:14:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be determined by the one thing\Neverybody agrees on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.93,0:14:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.10,0:14:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all these are worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest is nothing but fancy\Nwords to add appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.51,0:14:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is money... God?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.64,0:14:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's power. Something a lot\Nmore useful than God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.68,0:14:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock. Besides this,\Nwhat do you put value on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.55,0:14:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God? Love? Don't make me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.86,0:14:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when I was a brat, and crawling\Nthe streets of that dump...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.83,0:14:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...for whatever reason, God and love\Nwere always out of stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.07,0:14:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I knew better,\NI clung to and cried out to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I believed in God...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.24,0:14:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...right up to the day cops beat the hell\Noutta me for something I didn't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just because I lived\Nin a poor neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.08,0:14:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With no power and no God,\Nwhat can a Chinese bitch rely on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.89,0:15:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's money. And guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.09,0:15:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With those two things,\Nthe world's a great place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.57,0:15:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather not have heard that. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.80,0:15:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.94,0:15:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I wanted pity I would've added\Nmore color to the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.14,0:15:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moral of the story is that when\Nyou're living on life's edge...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.88,0:15:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that's all that matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.28,0:15:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not everybody can get off\Non being normal, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.19,0:15:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.99,0:15:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are wealthy fat bastards\Nliving by palm trees...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.39,0:15:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and bitches who think putting on\Nmakeup is life's greatest work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.53,0:15:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you speaking your mind from\Nthe same viewpoint as those hypocrites.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.94,0:15:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing worse than being treated\Nlike a whore by your companions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.68,0:15:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the next time you try telling me what's\Nproper, you'll no longer be one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.85,0:16:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When that happens... I'm gonna kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.96,0:16:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.30,0:16:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy. What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.97,0:16:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.31,0:16:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go somewhere where bullets won't\Nfind you, and keep quiet, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.58,0:16:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones that knock on a door\Nin a place like this are ghosts or villains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.65,0:16:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And since ghosts don't\Nexist in this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.68,0:16:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that would mean we've\Ngot troublemakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We left our gear on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.63,0:16:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one passageway.\NThere's no escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.84,0:16:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.61,0:16:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.38,0:16:59.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.41,0:17:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock, you have a lot to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.71,0:17:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What you need to listen for are\Nthe guns on their belts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.42,0:17:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.39,0:17:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.56,0:17:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, that's obvious. Kill them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.36,0:17:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock, get our air!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.23,0:17:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grave-robbers. There are two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.44,0:17:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,John! Around to the other side!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.14,0:17:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock! Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.58,0:17:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. The painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.45,0:17:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Brunhilda. We got it!\NCover me. I'm off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.93,0:17:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They got the painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.06,0:17:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.53,0:17:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not getting away that easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.40,0:17:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disconnect the pod!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.60,0:17:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Richert and the others\Nare still down there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.37,0:18:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget them.\NThey're already dead. Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.81,0:18:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run Rock! We need to get to our gear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The beacons are on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.42,0:18:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.55,0:18:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Directly above the submarine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.73,0:18:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are they doing?\NWhere are they going?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.93,0:18:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their position isn't changing.\NThey're going straight up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.67,0:18:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Towards the Nazi mother ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.97,0:18:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did it, Captain. We have the painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.71,0:18:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You did well!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.38,0:18:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we have enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She can't be planning to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.45,0:18:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy and Rock don't know who they're\Nup against. She's probably gonna do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.42,0:18:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. These guys shoot\Nanti-tank missiles without warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.26,0:18:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy's equipment isn't gonna be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.53,0:19:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she surfaces without a clue,\Nit's gonna be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.30,0:19:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet. It's too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.40,0:19:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Dutch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.97,0:19:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want to show some bravado,\Ncharge in, and all go to hell together?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.88,0:19:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may paint a great picture, but it won't\Nbe much of an ending, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.45,0:19:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just pray that\NRevy hasn't snapped yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.12,0:19:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The grave robbers are coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.82,0:19:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The grave robbers are coming up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.79,0:19:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready to fire the machine gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.46,0:19:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.00,0:19:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They started.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.10,0:19:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.80,0:19:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If they're still shooting,{\i0}\N{\i1}it means they're alive.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.73,0:20:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've stopped shooting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.63,0:20:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Looks that way.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.60,0:20:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We got them! They've sunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.33,0:20:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.60,0:20:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was your misfortune to touch our\Nglorious inheritance with your dirty hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.94,0:20:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can regret it at\Nthe bottom of the dark sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.57,0:20:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Retrieve the pod. We're leaving this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.14,0:20:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The beacons are still active. They're\Ndrifting southeast, away from the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.88,0:20:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell whether they're dead or alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.85,0:20:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you hear me, Dutch?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.76,0:20:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah. Their mother ship is moving.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.66,0:20:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we go and pick up some bones?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.96,0:20:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's a harsh remark, boy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.90,0:20:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My nerves aren't as tough as yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.30,0:20:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.74,0:20:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy, look. There's our boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.75,0:20:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So they got away with the goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.58,0:21:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are they?\NThose bald bastards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.45,0:21:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're Nazis.\NLeftovers from the dark ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.52,0:21:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know which country\Nthey came from, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.33,0:21:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, this isn't funny.\NThe skinheads got one over us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.06,0:21:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not over yet, Revy.\NThe job we took on isn't finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.84,0:21:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it, Dutch! Let's turn\Nthe Nazi Party into a bloody party.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.87,0:21:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.14,0:21:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Putting politics aside, it's not good for\Nbusiness to let them have it their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.31,0:21:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiots playing heroes need some bitter\Nmedicine. Let's give it to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.55,0:21:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.56,0:23:18.53,Black Lagoon Next Episode,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur10\pos(980,916)}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.27,0:23:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Dutch, it's just not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.14,0:23:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't partner with him.
